<h1><font color="\&quot;#222222\&quot;" face="\&quot;Arial," tahoma,="" helvetica,="" freesans,="" sans-serif\"=""><span style="\&quot;font-size:" 21.81818199157715px;\"="">A monadic formlet example</span></font></h1><div><br></div><div class="\&quot;post-body" entry-content\"="" id="\&quot;post-body-78074708202927443\&quot;" itemprop="\&quot;description" articlebody\"="" style="\&quot;width:" 730px;="" font-size:="" 13px;="" line-height:="" 1.4;="" position:="" relative;="" color:="" rgb(34,="" 34,="" 34);="" font-family:="" arial,="" tahoma,="" helvetica,="" freesans,="" sans-serif;="" background-color:="" rgb(255,="" 255,="" 255);\"=""><div style="\&quot;text-align:" justify;\"=""><a href="\&quot;https://www.google.es/search?q=formlets+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=d9LCUcenLsGphAeRqoH4BA\&quot;" style="\&quot;text-decoration:" none;="" color:="" rgb(136,="" 136,="" 136);\"="">Formlets</a>&nbsp;are about&nbsp;<a href="\&quot;https://www.google.es/search?q=Applicative+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=utLCUcnKFo6ZhQfM64GgBA\&quot;" style="\&quot;text-decoration:" none;="" color:="" rgb(136,="" 136,="" 136);\"="">applicative</a>&nbsp;instances, but what about&nbsp;<a href="\&quot;https://www.google.es/search?q=monad+haskell&amp;sourceid=ie7&amp;rls=com.microsoft:en-US:IE-Address&amp;ie=&amp;oe=&amp;redir_esc=&amp;ei=-9LCUfaKGc6DhQedroCACQ\&quot;" style="\&quot;text-decoration:" none;="" color:="" rgb(136,="" 136,="" 136);\"="">monadic</a>&nbsp;instances? What a Monad instance of formlets means? I recently experimented with this and the results are very interesting -and powerful-. It mixes the best of web forms, with the flexibility of console applications.&nbsp;<br><br>Since the monad instance of the MFlow widgets (The View monad) stop at the first widget not validated or empty, and because a monad can manipulate output values of the widgets and therefore the result can be presented along the widget inputs, then the resulting interface is a mix of a console application, an spreadsheet and a dynamic HTML application that is programmed in plain simple imperative style without the need of javascript to achieve the dynamic behaviour</div></div>